				<name type="string">Single-Weapon Style</name>
			</id-00001>
			<id-00002>
				<blocks>
					<id-00003>
						<blocktype type="string">singletext</blocktype>
						<frame type="string">sidebar</frame>
						<order type="number">1</order>
						<text type="formattedtext">
							<p>
								<b>Single-Weapon Style:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>AC: + 1 with any (prof) one-handed weapon.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Two-Handed Style:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Speed Factor -3 with any (prof) 2-handed weapon.</li>
								<li>Certain 1-handed weapons can be wielded 2-handed for +1 dmg.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Weapon and Shield Style:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Extra attack with shield punch/parry at standard -2/-4 attack penalty.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Two-Weapon Style:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Bonus when fighting with two weapons -0/-2.</li>
								<li>Ambidextrous -0/-0.</li>
								<li>Can wield two same size weapons (i.e. 2x longswords)&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00106@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Reference Manaul:</link>
							</linklist>
						</text>
					</id-00003>
				</blocks>
				<name type="string">Fighting Styles Summary</name>
			</id-00002>
			<id-00003>
				<blocks>
					<id-00001>
						<blocktype type="string">singletext</blocktype>
						<frame type="string">sidebar</frame>
						<order type="number">1</order>
						<text type="formattedtext">
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00117@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">
									<b>Called Shot - Standard Modifier</b>
								</link>
							</linklist>
							<list>
								<li>+1 Penalty to Initiative</li>
								<li>-4 Penalty to Hit</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>&#13;&#13;Disarm Single Handed Weapons:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Called Shot.</li>
								<li>Weapon lands 2d6ft away at 1d6 direction relative to attacker.</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="table" recordname="tables.id-00001@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Table: Disarm vs. Single-Handed Weapons</link>
							</linklist>
							<p>
								<b>&#13;Disarm Two-Handed Weapon:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Called Shot.</li>
								<li>1st succes knocks weapon out of alignment.</li>
								<li>Next round lose init unless extra attack used to fix grip.</li>
								<li>2nd success you've disarmed foe.</li>
								<li>Weapon lands 1d6ft away at 1d6 direction.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Shield:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>Called Shot.</li>
								<li>Knock shield out of alignment.</li>
								<li>Enemy looses shield bonus for rest of round.</li>
								<li>May use extra attack to fix grip on shield, ending the effect.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Thrown-Weapons and Missile Disarm:</b>
							</p>
							<list>
								<li>More difficult (S) size weapons @ additional -6 attack.</li>
								<li>Won't work against two-handed weapons&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<p>
								<b>Expert Disarm:</b>
							</p>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00124@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Expert Disarms</link>
							</linklist>
							<list>
								<li>+2 Initiative.</li>
								<li>-8 to hit.</li>
								<li>On success, send weapon anywhere you want within 12ft.&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00118@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Striking a specific body part.</link>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00119@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Smashing something being held.</link>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00120@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Bypassing armor.</link>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00121@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Special usage.</link>
							</linklist>
						</text>
					</id-00001>
				</blocks>
				<name type="string">Called Shots Summary</name>
			</id-00003>
			<id-00004>
				<blocks />
			</id-00004>
			<id-00005>
				<blocks>
					<id-00001>
						<blocktype type="string">singletext</blocktype>
						<frame type="string">sidebar</frame>
						<order type="number">1</order>
						<text type="formattedtext">
							<p>
								<b>Grab</b>
							</p>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00125@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Grab</link>
							</linklist>
							<list>
								<li>Trying to grab something/someone, called shot roll and oppose strength.</li>
								<li>Both characters roll strength checks, whoever won their check better snatches the item/gets the hold.</li>
								<li>Lots of factors/variables&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00127@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Grabbing a Monster</link>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00126@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Grabbing A Person</link>
							</linklist>
						</text>
					</id-00001>
				</blocks>
				<name type="string">Grabbing Summary</name>
			</id-00005>
			<id-00006>
				<blocks>
					<id-00001>
						<blocktype type="string">singletext</blocktype>
						<frame type="string">sidebar</frame>
						<order type="number">1</order>
						<text type="formattedtext">
							<p>
								<b>Hold attack:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Just hit delay for your action.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Parry (special):</b>
							</p>
							<p>Roll hit vs. attacker. If success, attacker no damage. Must call upfront how many of your attacks will be parries. Polearm parries vs. people who aren't attacking you is an interesting concept. Can't parry missile attacks but can parry thrown weapons. Using a missile weapon to parry, like a bow, on success weapon breaks. Page 70.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Pin:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Try to pin a character's weapon arm, ect. -4 to hit, no init penalty. If successful, the enemy can't use their pinned weapon until pin is broken + you can't use the weapon you're using to pin. Round 1 - one chance - oppose strength like grab - if success can use all his remaining attacks and break free. If fail, the weapon pinned for rest of round, lose one of his attacks. Next round+ struggle/break roll does not count against attacks. Page 71.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Pull/Trip: </b>&#13;Knockdown - declare upfront or on turn. Describe. IF possible, normal attack. Then the enemy makes DEX check. See modifiers and use common sense to adjust. +6 target not moving, -3 target unaware of attack, ect. Page 71.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Sap:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Hitting over head to knockout. Must announce upfront, called shot @ -8 to hit. See Page 72.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Sheild Punch:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Normal attack roll, no bonus, dmg 1-3 + str bonus, rest of round you lose your shield AC, Good when you've dropped your weapon, or have your weapon pinned, ect. Page 72.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Shield Rush:</b>
							</p>
							<p>A combo of pull/trip and shield punch. 10ft away minimum, medium or greater size shield. Basically, run at target with hope of injuring or knocking down. Page 72.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Surprise and Flash Maneuvers:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Page 73.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Martial Arts:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Page 74 - 80.&#13;</p>
							<p>
								<b>Hit Locations:</b>
							</p>
							<p>Page 80.</p>
						</text>
					</id-00001>
				</blocks>
				<name type="string">Misc Combat Maneuvers </name>
			</id-00006>
			<id-00007>
				<blocks>
					<id-00001>
						<blocktype type="string">singletext</blocktype>
						<frame type="string">sidebar</frame>
						<order type="number">1</order>
						<text type="formattedtext">
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00106@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Story: The Four Fighting Styles</link>
							</linklist>
							<h>Fighting styles...</h>
							<list>
								<li>
									<b>Single-weapon style</b> - AC: 1 w/ prof(1h)</li>
								<li>
									<b>Two-handed style</b> - Speed -3 w/prof(2h). 1h wielded 2h +1 dmg</li>
								<li>
									<b>Weapon and shield style</b> - extra attk w/shield punch/parray @-2/-4</li>
								<li>
									<b>Two-weapon style</b> - 2w -0/-2. Ambidexrious -0/-0. Wield same size weapon&#13;</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00117@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Story: Called Shots</link>
							</linklist>
							<h>Called Shots...</h>
							<list>
								<li>
									<b>Standrd called shot</b> - +1 to init/-4 to hit ---&#62;</li>
								<li>Striking a specific body part </li>
								<li>Smashing something being held </li>
								<li>Bypassing armor (finding the weakness, not ignoring armor class, see details)</li>
								<li>
									<b>Disarm..</b>
								</li>
								<li>
									<b>A single handed weapon</b> - w/ lands 2d6ft away at 1d6dir.</li>
								<li>
									<b>A two-handed weapon</b> - 1st knock out-of-alignment. Use extra attack to fix grip or loose init next round fixing grip. W/ fully disarmed on 2 successes. Lands 1d6ft away at 1d6dir.</li>
								<li>
									<b>A shield</b> - Knock shield out-of-alignment. Loose AC bonus rest round. Can use ext attack to fix grip.</li>
								<li>
									<b>Thrown-weapon/missile disarm </b>- only works vs. 1h weapons. Size (S) weapons @ -2 atk penalty.</li>
								<li>
									<b>Expert Disarm </b>- +2 to init/-8 to hit - send weapon anwhere you want in 12ft.</li>
								<li>
									<b>Grab</b> - On called shot success, hands on target, but .. opposed str check (who passed by more). See more detail below.</li>
							</list>
							<linklist>
								<link class="referencemanualpage" recordname="reference.refmanualdata.id-00125@AD&amp;D 2E Complete Fighter's Handbook">Story: Grab</link>
							</linklist>
							<p />
